\fs36 \cf0 Making Changes
\fs24 \
There are various minor changes you can make to the settings to tweak this template so that it better suits your needs, as follows:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj
\ls8\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}
\b Project and author name:
\b0  The default book title and author name used in headers and elsewhere can be customised by going to Project > Meta-Data Settings\'85 and choosing the \'93Project Properties\'94 tab.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li720\fi-720\sl360\slmult1\pardirnatural\qj
\ls8\ilvl0
\b \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Chapter subtitles: 
\b0 If you don\'92t want to include the names of your chapter folders below the chapter numbering text in the compiled document, go to the \'93Formatting\'94 pane in the \'93All Options\'94 tab of the Compile sheet and deselect \'93Title\'94 in the list of elements to include.\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b Page header and footer: 
\b0 You can edit the page header in the \'93Page Settings\'94 pane of the Compile sheet (under \'93All Options\'94).\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b Page size: 
\b0 The \'93Paperback Novel\'94 format is set to export to a page size of 5.06\'94 x 7.81\'94, which is one of the formats you can use with CreateSpace. You can customise this by clicking on the \'93Page Setup\'85\'94 button in the \'93Page Settings\'94 pane of Compile.\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b Font:
\b0  You can use \'93Quick Font Override\'94 in Compile to change the font used throughout the final document (this is available from both the \'93Summary\'94 and \'93All Options\'94 tabs). Note that fonts are not included in e-books, however\'97e-readers choose their own fonts (and you would need to pay a hefty fee for a licence to embed a particular font in an e-book).\
{\listtext	\'95	}
\b Making your own special folders:
